As for that article, when I was around 5 or so, a friend of mine and I were playing some version of war with cap guns. This was back when we had toy guns that looked like guns. Not fruity rainbows. After a long gun battle on my grandparents balcony, we ran out of caps and resorted to killing each other with rubber knives. Well, we got a little rough and iI was knocked off the 3rd story balcony. I landed on the grill below with only one foot taking the impact then busted my head on the concrete. I broke several bones in my leg and needed 12 stiches to close my head. I also walked with a limp for 6 years after this. No charges filed, no one went to jail, no one was sued. We were kids being kids. To this day, im still very good friends with the guy who crippled me for years.<br>
<br>
Morale of the story, kids will be kids. If you try to keep them from being kids, they become adults who never had a childhood. Just like David Berkowitz<br>
